<h3 id="cp-8-telecommunications-services-m-h">CP-8 Telecommunications Services (M) (H)</h3>
<p>The organization establishes alternate telecommunications services including necessary agreements to permit the resumption of [Assignment: organization-defined information system operations] for essential missions and business functions within [FedRAMP Assignment: See CP-8 additional FedRAMP requirements and guidance] when the primary telecommunications capabilities are unavailable at either the primary or alternate processing or storage sites.<br />
<b>CP-8 Additional FedRAMP Requirements and Guidance:</b><br />
<b>Requirement:</b> The service provider defines a time period consistent with the recovery time objectives and business impact analysis.</p>

